OL,3,CSchool secretaries and caretakers
OL,4,Cbegin indefinite strike
OL,6,FAfter a union-led campaign several
OL,7,Fyears ago, secretaries in most schools
OL,8,Fwere put on the public payroll in
OL,9,F2022, meaning they no longer had to
OL,10,Fsign on to social welfare during the
OL,11,Fsummer holidays and became entitled to
OL,12,Fsick pay and maternity leave.
OL,14,FAlthough they are now being paid
OL,15,Fdirectly by the Department, most are
OL,16,Fnot classified as public servants.
